The Aphalarinae is strongly supported as a monophylum in molecular analyses (
Percy et al . 2018
;
Cho et al . 2019
), morphologically ( Loginova 1964 ; Brown & Hodkinson 1988 ; Burckhardt & Queiroz 2013 ;
Ouvrard et al . 2013
) and by the pattern of sperm formation (
Labina et al . 2014
). The subfamily includes two monophyletic tribes: the extant Aphalarini and the extinct Paleopsylloidini †.
